# signoz_auth_domain (Data Source)

Reads a single SigNoz auth domain by ID.

## Example Usage

{{tffile "examples/data-sources/signoz_auth_domain/data-source.tf"}}

<!-- schema generated by tfplugindocs -->

## Schema

### Required

- `id` (String) ID of the auth domain to look up.

### Read-Only

- `auth_nprovider_info` (Attributes) Provider metadata including SAML relay-state path.
- `created_at` (String) Creation timestamp.
- `google_auth_config` (Attributes) Active Google OAuth config (sensitive fields elided).
- `name` (String) Email domain.
- `oidc_config` (Attributes) Active OIDC config.
- `org_id` (String) Org ID.
- `role_mapping` (Attributes) Active role mapping.
- `saml_config` (Attributes) Active SAML config.
- `sso_enabled` (Boolean) Whether SSO is enabled.
- `sso_type` (String) Currently selected SSO type.
- `updated_at` (String) Last-update timestamp.

Nested attribute shapes mirror the resource's read-only `*_config` blocks. See `signoz_auth_domain` (Resource) for details.
